{"key":"processedPost-7778829","value":{"id":7778829,"first":7777985,"last":7780526,"when":1198114753,"utime":"12/20/07 03:39 AM","content":"It has less than a 50/50 chance, depending on the endospore count of the grains you're using.  Some batches of grain have higher bacterial endospore counts than others.  Another reason for the high failure ratio is that many endospores upon germination, produce more endospores within hours.<br /><br />I'd suggest pressure cooking, but if you're determined to use fractional sterilization, use a pot with a very tight fitting lid, and have the water no more than half way up the jars.  Put foil over the lids. I' also boil for 2 hours each time instead of the usual 1.<br />RR","title":"Re: how to boil jars? wet filter?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}